history.content: I took Math 55 with her and I would say any class in the Math department with Olga Holtz may as well be considered an honors math class and will have much higher workload than normal. That being said however, if you put enough work into it, it will be super rewarding. Just be prepared for super difficult problem sets in both classes cause Professor Holtz likes hand-picking the hardest questions imaginable each week and 170 problem sets are often notoriously long and difficult. If you were to take a third technical course, definitely take a lower workload class.
How is the workload for CS170 and Math 110 (with Olga Holtz)? Would it be feasible to take those two courses with another technical?
